<bdy>

<b>Aktion Kinder des Holocaust</b> also known by its initials <b>AKdH</b>  is an international community of descendants of survivors of the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../793/10396793.xml">
Holocaust</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../927/32927.xml">
World War 2</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../045/646045.xml">
antifascist</link> resistance, together with their relatives and friends. <ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> It is constituted as a club under under Article 60ff CC of Swiss law. It describes himself as "association against anti-Semitism, racism and political extremism." It's name translates as <it>Action (by) Children of the Holocaust</it>.<p>

It was founded in 1991 around an interdisciplinary research project associated with the <body wordnetid="107965085" confidence="0.8">
<university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.8">
<social_group wordnetid="107950920" confidence="0.8">
<educational_institution wordnetid="108276342" confidence="0.8">
<group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
